The paper deals with optimization problems in a stochastic probing setting, which involves selecting a subset of items to probe based on their probabilities of success. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the performance of the algorithms. The paper deals with approximation algorithms and their analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.SI).
